contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} The '''White Oak Pocosin''' is a large swamp in northern [[Onslow County, North Carolina|Onslow County]] and southern [[Jones County, North Carolina|Jones County]], [[North Carolina]] in the [[United States]]. It provides the headwaters of the [[White Oak River]]. The word [[pocosin]] is a [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] word meaning "swamp". {{Coord|34|56|02|N|77|25|58|W|display=title}} [[Category:Geography of Jones County, North Carolina]] [[Category:Wetlands of North Carolina]] [[Category:Geography of Onslow County, North Carolina]] [[Category:Swamps of the United States]] {{NorthCarolina-geo-stub}}
